text: The Electoral district of Morven was a single-member electoral district of the Tasmanian House of Assembly. It centred on the town of Evandale to the south of Launceston. The seat was created ahead of the Assembly's first election held in 1856, and was renamed Evandale at the 1886 election. ==Members for Morven== {| class="wikitable" |- !Member!!Term |- | Frederick Innes | 1856–1862 |- | Alexander Rose | 1862–1866 |- | John Gleadow | 1866–1869 |- | John Whitehead | 1869–1880 |- | James Cox | 1880–1882 |- | John Falkiner | 1882–1886 |} ==References== * * * Parliament of Tasmania (2006).
